article.headline: Dartmouth 66, Quinnipiac 61
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- David Gardner scored 17 points and added seven rebounds to lead Dartmouth over Quinnipiac 66-61 Tuesday. Dartmouth pulled ahead for good, 58-56, with 5:05 left as Gardner made three of four free throws and Johnathan Ball had three layups. Quinnipiac (2-1) led 32-25 at halftime before the Big Green (1-0) answered with a 13-5 run. Leon Pattman had a pair of free throws as Dartmouth pushed ahead, 38-37, with 14:14 left. The Bobcats regained the lead, 54-49, with 8:26 left on a 3-pointer by Rob Monroe. But the Big Green responded with a 9-2 run. Gardner led four Dartmouth players in double figures, including Pattman, with 11, and Ball and Michael Lang, with 10 each. Monroe led Quinnipiac with 21 points. It was the Big Green's first season-opening win since 1999.
